  "rendered": {
    "title": "Remote chat resilience and a more observable Windows updater",
    "intro": "Today's nightly hardens the remote chat path end-to-end and tightens up the Windows auto-update handoff. On the server, sessions now carry the right org identity and stalled remote streams surface real errors instead of hanging on \"connecting.\" On the desktop side, the Windows updater is more observable and runs off the runtime thread, while the interface gets steadier chat tails, sidebar previews, and composer focus.",
    "entries": [
      {
        "batch_id": "entry-1",
        "time_label": "2:37 PM",
        "started_at": "2026-05-02T21:37:08.000Z",
        "ended_at": "2026-05-02T21:37:08.000Z",
        "title": "Org identity preserved for remote harness chats",
        "summary": "Remote chat sessions now derive the X-Aura-Org-Id header from the project when the agent record is missing it, keeping org-scoped integrations working.",
        "items": [
          {
            "text": "Chat routes fall back to the project's org id when agent metadata is incomplete, so remote harness sessions consistently send X-Aura-Org-Id and resolve installed integrations against the correct org.",
            "commit_shas": [
              "9bbe1ae4500f19f6a7e2f9fc278293b40c372761"
            ],
            "confidence": "high"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "batch_id": "entry-2",
        "time_label": "2:40 PM",
        "started_at": "2026-05-02T21:40:29.000Z",
        "ended_at": "2026-05-02T21:40:29.000Z",
        "title": "Windows updater handoff: logs, relaunch, and single-instance retry",
        "summary": "The NSIS-based Windows updater now captures handoff logs, waits for the prior instance to exit, and relaunches Aura after install instead of disappearing silently.",
        "items": [
          {
            "text": "Windows updates write a per-version handoff log and PowerShell script next to the staged installer, so failed or silent updates leave behind diagnostics instead of vanishing.",
            "commit_shas": [
              "b7d61680e560cbca7b1df6f3ec16c783705f7fff"
            ],
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "text": "When relaunched after an install, Aura retries the single-instance mutex for up to 15 seconds via a new AURA_UPDATE_RELAUNCH signal, avoiding races where the old process hasn't fully exited yet.",
            "commit_shas": [
              "b7d61680e560cbca7b1df6f3ec16c783705f7fff"
            ],
            "confidence": "high"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "batch_id": "entry-3",
        "time_label": "2:55 PM",
        "started_at": "2026-05-02T21:55:05.000Z",
        "ended_at": "2026-05-02T21:55:05.000Z",
        "title": "Stalled remote chat streams now fail loudly instead of spinning",
        "summary": "A new turn watchdog and stricter Swarm session startup turn silent remote runtimes into explicit errors, so the UI stops getting stuck on the connecting state.",
        "items": [
          {
            "text": "Swarm session startup now waits for an explicit session_ready signal, and a turn watchdog broadcasts synthetic terminal errors if the remote agent emits no events within 30 seconds or stalls past the 5-minute turn ceiling.",
            "commit_shas": [
              "33ad453f9e8aa1af16d78e0837800f09d16bec15"
            ],
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "text": "The WebSocket bridge now rejects unsupported frames with a clear error path instead of silently dropping them, surfacing protocol mismatches to the chat UI.",
            "commit_shas": [
              "33ad453f9e8aa1af16d78e0837800f09d16bec15"
            ],
            "confidence": "medium"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "batch_id": "entry-4",
        "time_label": "2:56 PM",
        "started_at": "2026-05-02T21:56:36.000Z",
        "ended_at": "2026-05-02T21:56:36.000Z",
        "title": "Updater installs run on a dedicated OS thread",
        "summary": "The user-approved install no longer piggybacks on the Tokio runtime, and the Windows smoke test can recover a version when PE metadata is empty.",
        "items": [
          {
            "text": "start_install now spawns a named aura-update-install OS thread instead of a Tokio task, removing the need for a reactor on the tao event loop and simplifying lifecycle when the app is shutting down for the install.",
            "commit_shas": [
              "9e665002e20c855d8954d65ed69b7823b7b8af45"
            ],
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "text": "The Windows auto-update smoke script falls back to the NSIS uninstall registry's DisplayVersion when ProductVersion and FileVersion are both blank, so older installer artifacts don't break release verification.",
            "commit_shas": [
              "9e665002e20c855d8954d65ed69b7823b7b8af45"
            ],
            "confidence": "high"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "batch_id": "entry-5",
        "time_label": "2:59 PM",
        "started_at": "2026-05-02T21:59:52.000Z",
        "ended_at": "2026-05-02T22:06:36.000Z",
        "title": "Steadier chat tail and sidebar previews",
        "summary": "Two interface fixes stop end-of-turn flicker in the chat transcript and keep agent sidebar previews stable as history caches roll over.",
        "items": [
          {
            "text": "The final assistant bubble now uses a content-derived render key, so when persisted history replaces the streaming placeholder the tail row keeps the same DOM node and stops flashing at end of turn.",
            "commit_shas": [
              "0dbf9681172ba6b7c18b996948965eb14fd1d15b"
            ],
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "text": "The agent list reads previews from a dedicated previewLastMessages cache (capped at 100 entries) instead of the bounded 8-entry history store, so sidebar previews stay populated even after older history entries are evicted.",
            "commit_shas": [
              "a33f494041f19908a4d4ab1c52bb3e01e8a5f1cc"
            ],
            "confidence": "high"
          }
        ]
